---
title: "Creating a website"
format: 
  html: 
    highlight-style: dracula
---

## Create a new Rstudio project

1.  In the terminal, type `quarto create project`
2.  Select wesbite by using the down arrows and enter
3.  Set directory as `.` (to create the website in the 'project' folder rather than a subfolder inside that)
4.  choose a title
5.  once your documents have been created, reload posit cloud to get the 'build' button

## Editing the \_quarto.yml

Example:

``` r
project:
  type: website
  output-dir: docs

website:
  title: "R Guide"
  navbar:
    left:
      - text: "Home"
        href: index.qmd
      - text: "Analysing Data"
        href: posts/analysing_data.qmd
      - text: "Creating a blog"
        href: posts/blog.qmd
      - text: "Blogs"
        menu: 
          - href: https://ks745.quarto.pub/r-guide/posts/blog.html
            text: "R blog"
          - href: https://ks745.quarto.pub/qqm/
            text: "QQM"
          - href: https://ks745.quarto.pub/discovering-statistics/
            text: "Discovering Statistics"

    tools:
      - icon: cloudy-fill
        href: https://posit.cloud/content/yours?sort=name_asc

  sidebar:
    - title: "Analysing Data"
      style: "docked"
      contents:
        - text: "Analysing Data"
          href: posts/analysing_data.qmd
        - section: "Visualising Data"
          href: posts/summary_tables.qmd
          contents:
            - posts/summary_tables.qmd
            - posts/plots.qmd
            - posts/diagnostic_info.qmd
        - text: "Linear Model"
          href: posts/lm.qmd
        - text: "Contrast Coding"
          href: posts/contrast_coding.qmd
        - text: "Exploratory Factor Analysis"
          href: posts/efa.qmd
    
    - title: "Creating a blog"
      contents: 
        - posts/blog.qmd
        - posts/website.qmd
format:
  html:
    theme:
       light: minty
       dark: solar
    css: styles.css
    toc: true
```

This website: <https://quarto.org/docs/websites/website-navigation.html#side-navigation> has lots of ways to customise the \_quarto.yml doc to get the website to look how you want
